# AfterThought — Codeplain Specification

> AI Meeting Memory Engine. A Next.js 16 (App Router) web app + PWA, a Manifest V3
> browser extension that records audio, and a Supabase (Postgres + Auth) backend.
> This `.plain` file documents the repository as it currently exists. It is
> documentation only — it does not change any code.

---

## 1. Project Overview

**AfterThought** records, transcribes, and organizes meetings automatically,
turning conversations into searchable summaries, action items, speaker insights,
and mind maps.

The system has three runtime surfaces that share one Supabase backend:

- **Web app (Next.js App Router + PWA)** — the marketing site, authentication
  pages, and the authenticated dashboard where meetings, insights, speakers,
  calendar events, and follow-up templates are viewed.
- **Browser extension (Manifest V3)** — captures microphone audio in a dedicated
  tab and uploads it to the backend for processing, authenticated with the
  user's Supabase access token.
- **Backend (Next.js Route Handlers + Supabase)** — validates bearer tokens,
  persists meetings scoped per user, and exposes read APIs for the dashboard.

The product is built around real authentication and per-user data ownership.
The AI transcription/summarization pipeline is intentionally a **placeholder**
(scaffolding) so the surrounding architecture can be exercised end to end.

**Key behaviors:**

- Email + password authentication (plus magic-link) via Supabase Auth.
- Per-user data ownership enforced at two layers: application-code `user_id`
  scoping (service-role API routes) and database Row Level Security (anon key).
- Graceful **demo mode**: when Supabase env vars are absent, the app still builds
  and runs with auth disabled so local development and previews never break.

---

## 2. High-Level Architecture

```
                         ┌──────────────────────────────┐
                         │        Supabase (cloud)        │
                         │  Postgres + Auth + RLS         │
                         └───────────────┬────────────────┘
                                         │
            service-role key             │  anon key + access token
       (server, bypasses RLS,            │  (browser session)
        enforces user_id in code)        │
                                         │
   ┌──────────────────────┐     ┌────────┴───────────┐     ┌──────────────────────┐
   │  Browser Extension   │     │   Next.js Backend   │     │   Next.js Frontend    │
   │  (Manifest V3)       │────▶│   Route Handlers    │◀────│   (App Router + PWA)   │
   │  records audio,      │ POST│   /api/*            │ GET │   dashboard, auth,     │
   │  Bearer token upload │     │   token validation  │     │   marketing site       │
   └──────────────────────┘     └─────────────────────┘     └──────────────────────┘
```

- **Frontend** and **Backend** live in the same Next.js project (`app/`).
- The **extension** is a separate, framework-less MV3 bundle in `extension/`.
- A `scripts/build.js` esbuild orchestrator exists for an Electron desktop app
  and a TSX extension popup; these source trees (`desktop-app/`,
  `extension/popup.tsx`) are **not present** in the repo and are documented as
  aspirational/unused (see Known Limitations).

---

## 3. Frontend Architecture (Next.js App Router)

The frontend uses the Next.js App Router with **route groups** to separate two
distinct chromes under a single root layout.

### Root layout
- `app/layout.tsx` — Loads Geist / Geist Mono fonts, sets metadata + viewport,
  applies the dark `bg-background` html class, mounts `AuthProvider` (global auth
  context) and Vercel `Analytics`. It contains **no** app navigation, so
  marketing and auth pages render full-bleed.
- `app/globals.css` — Tailwind v4 theme tokens (liquid-glass dark palette,
  neon-blue primary accent, pink micro-accent), `.glass`, `.glass-neon`,
  `.neon-glow` utility classes, and font variables.

### Route group: `(app)` — authenticated dashboard
- `app/(app)/layout.tsx` — Mounts the dashboard chrome: `TopNav`, the centered
  `<main>` container, `FloatingAssistant`, and wraps children in `AuthGate`
  (redirects unauthenticated users to `/sign-in` when Supabase is configured).
- Pages (URLs are unchanged by the group):
  - `app/(app)/page.tsx` — `/` Dashboard; lists meetings via `authFetch('/api/meetings')`.
  - `app/(app)/search/page.tsx` — `/search` global search UI.
  - `app/(app)/insights/page.tsx` — `/insights` analytics (topics, sentiment, mentions).
  - `app/(app)/speakers/page.tsx` — `/speakers` speaker directory (fetches `/api/speakers`).
  - `app/(app)/speakers/[id]/page.tsx` — `/speakers/:id` speaker detail.
  - `app/(app)/calendar/page.tsx` — `/calendar` action-item calendar (fetches `/api/calendar`).
  - `app/(app)/templates/page.tsx` — `/templates` follow-up email templates (fetches `/api/templates`).
  - `app/(app)/settings/page.tsx` — `/settings` profile, sign out, and the
    "Extension access" token card.
  - `app/(app)/meeting/[id]/page.tsx` — `/meeting/:id` meeting detail (`authFetch`).
  - `app/(app)/recording/[id]/page.tsx` — `/recording/:id` processed-recording view (`authFetch`).

### Marketing + auth (outside the group, no app chrome)
- `app/home/page.tsx` — `/home` marketing landing page composed of section
  components (`Hero`, `FeaturesGrid`, `HowItWorks`, `TechStack`, `Screenshots`,
  `Team`, `CtaBand`) plus `MarketingNav` and `MarketingFooter`.
- `app/sign-in/page.tsx` — `/sign-in` standalone email+password sign-in form.
- `app/sign-up/page.tsx` — `/sign-up` standalone sign-up form.
- `app/auth/callback/page.tsx` — `/auth/callback` magic-link / email confirmation handler.
- `app/success/page.tsx` — `/success` post-login confirmation screen.
- `app/not-found.tsx` — global standalone animated 404.

### Client state & data fetching
- **Auth context**: `components/auth-provider.tsx` exposes `useAuth()`
  (`user`, `session`, `loading`, `configured`, `signIn`, `signUp`,
  `signInWithMagicLink`, `signOut`, `getAccessToken`).
- **Authenticated requests**: `lib/api-client.ts` `authFetch()` attaches the
  Supabase access token as a `Bearer` header to every protected API call.
- **Animations**: `framer-motion` drives the hero stagger, the reusable
  scroll-reveal wrapper (`components/marketing/reveal.tsx`), success, and 404.

### Shared / dashboard components
`components/top-nav.tsx`, `floating-assistant.tsx`, `glass-panel.tsx`,
`insight-card.tsx`, `summary-card.tsx`, `meeting-card.tsx`, `search-bar.tsx`,
`transcript-block.tsx`, `meeting-insights-transcript.tsx`, `mind-map-canvas.tsx`,
`mind-map-node.tsx`, `brand-logo.tsx`, `email-template.tsx`, and `ui/button.tsx`.

---

## 4. Backend Architecture (API Routes)

All backend logic is implemented as Next.js Route Handlers under `app/api/`.

### Authenticated, Supabase-backed (per-user)
- `app/api/transcribe/route.ts` — **POST**. Requires a valid bearer token
  (`getUserFromRequest`). Reads the raw audio `ArrayBuffer`, generates a UUID,
  produces a **placeholder** transcript/summary/action-items, and inserts a row
  into `meetings` stamped with `user_id`. Returns `{ ok, id }`. Contains
  commented scaffolding hooks for follow-up email, calendar events, and speaker
  profiles.
- `app/api/meetings/route.ts` — **GET**. Returns the caller's meetings ordered by
  `created_at desc`, filtered by `user_id`.
- `app/api/meeting/[id]/route.ts` — **GET**. Returns a single meeting scoped to
  `id` **and** `user_id`; 404 if not owned/found.
- `app/api/speakers/route.ts` — **GET**. Returns the caller's speakers; degrades
  to an empty list if the table does not yet exist.
- `app/api/calendar/route.ts` — **GET**. Returns the caller's calendar events;
  degrades to an empty list if the table does not yet exist.
- `app/api/templates/route.ts` — **GET**. Auth-gated; returns static placeholder
  follow-up email templates (no AI generation).

### Demo/static (no auth, fixture data from `lib/fakeData.ts`)
- `app/api/summary/route.ts` — **GET** placeholder summaries.
- `app/api/insights/route.ts` — **GET** placeholder insights/transcript/topics/etc.
- `app/api/mindmap/route.ts` — **GET** placeholder mind-map nodes.
- `app/api/search/route.ts` — **GET** `?q=` filters fixture transcript + summaries.

### Server helpers
- `lib/supabase.ts`
  - `supabaseAdmin()` — service-role client (server only, `persistSession:false`).
  - `getUserFromToken(token)` — validates a token, returns `User | null`, never throws.
  - `getUserFromRequest(req)` — extracts the `Authorization: Bearer` token and validates it.
- `lib/supabase-browser.ts`
  - `isSupabaseConfigured` — boolean derived from public env vars.
  - `supabaseBrowser()` — memoized anon client with persisted sessions; returns
    `null` when unconfigured (enables demo mode).

### Scaffolding libraries (placeholders, not yet wired into live flows)
- `lib/email.ts` — `sendFollowUpEmail()` logs intent only.
- `lib/calendar.ts` — calendar-event creation scaffolding.
- `lib/speakers.ts` — speaker-profile update scaffolding.

