## 13. Data Flow Diagram (text-based)

```
[Record]   Extension recording.js ── MediaRecorder ──▶ audio/webm Blob
                │ runtime message (upload-recording)
                ▼
           background.js ── reads chrome.storage.local token
                │ POST /api/transcribe  (Bearer token, audio/webm)
                ▼
[Persist]  /api/transcribe ── getUserFromRequest() ── supabaseAdmin()
                │ INSERT meetings { id, user_id, summary, action_items, segments }
                ▼
           Supabase Postgres (RLS-protected)
                ▲
                │ SELECT ... WHERE user_id = auth user
[Read]     /api/meetings, /api/meeting/[id], /api/speakers, /api/calendar
                ▲
                │ authFetch() with Bearer token
                │
[Render]   Dashboard pages ── React state ── glass UI

[Demo]     /api/summary | /api/insights | /api/mindmap | /api/search
                └─ lib/fakeData.ts ── static fixtures (no auth, no DB)
```

---

## 14. Build & Deployment Instructions

### Prerequisites
- Node.js 18+ and **pnpm** (repo uses `pnpm-lock.yaml`).
- A Supabase project (optional for demo mode, required for auth + persistence).

### Environment variables
| Variable                        | Used by            | Purpose                              |
|---------------------------------|--------------------|--------------------------------------|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`      | browser + server   | Supabase project URL                 |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | browser            | anon client (sessions, RLS access)   |
| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`     | server API routes  | service-role client (bypasses RLS)   |

When the public vars are absent, the app runs in **demo mode** (auth disabled,
`AuthGate` passes through, sign-in shows a "not configured" notice).

### Database setup
- Run `supabase/schema.sql` in the Supabase SQL editor (or as a migration) to
  create `meetings`, `speakers`, `calendar_events`, their indexes, and RLS
  policies. The script is idempotent.

### Local development
```
pnpm install
pnpm dev          # Next.js dev server (PWA service worker disabled in dev)
```

### Production build
```
pnpm build        # next build (+ next-pwa service worker generation)
pnpm start        # serve the production build
```

### Browser extension
- Load `extension/` as an unpacked MV3 extension (`chrome://extensions` →
  Developer mode → Load unpacked).
- In the popup, paste the access token from the web app's `/settings`
  "Extension access" card.
- The upload URL is hard-coded to `http://localhost:3000/api/transcribe`; update
  it for non-local backends.

### Deployment
- Deploy the Next.js app to Vercel; set the three environment variables in the
  project settings. `host_permissions` in the extension manifest already include
  `https://afterthought.vercel.app/*`.

### Other scripts (currently non-functional — see Known Limitations)
```
pnpm build:desktop   # scripts/build.js — expects desktop-app/ and extension/popup.tsx
pnpm desktop         # electron desktop-app/dist/main.js
```

---

## 15. Known Limitations

- **AI pipeline is a placeholder.** `/api/transcribe` returns hard-coded
  transcript, summary, and action items. No real STT/LLM is invoked.
- **Scaffolding not wired.** `lib/email.ts`, `lib/calendar.ts`, and
  `lib/speakers.ts` only log; the `transcribe` route's calls to them are
  commented out. `speakers`/`calendar` GET routes degrade to empty lists if
  their tables are absent.
- **Static demo endpoints.** `/api/summary`, `/api/insights`, `/api/mindmap`,
  and `/api/search` serve fixture data from `lib/fakeData.ts` and are not
  user-scoped or auth-gated.
- **Hard-coded extension URL.** The extension uploads to
  `http://localhost:3000/api/transcribe`; production use requires editing
  `background.js`.
- **Manual token handoff.** The extension is authenticated by copy-pasting the
  Supabase access token; there is no OAuth handshake, and tokens expire.
- **Desktop/Electron + TSX popup absent.** `scripts/build.js` references
  `desktop-app/` and `extension/popup.tsx` which do not exist in the repository,
  so `build:desktop` and `desktop` scripts will fail as-is.
- **Service-role in route handlers.** API routes use the service-role key and
  rely on application-code `user_id` filtering for ownership; a coding mistake
  there would not be caught by RLS (which only guards anon-key access).
- **No automated tests** are present in the repository.

---

## 16. Future Improvements

- Replace the placeholder pipeline with real speech-to-text (e.g. Whisper) and an
  LLM (GPT/Claude) for summaries, action items, and speaker diarization.
- Activate the scaffolding: send follow-up emails, create calendar events, and
  build speaker profiles automatically after transcription.
- Make demo endpoints (`summary`, `insights`, `mindmap`, `search`) read real,
  user-scoped data from Supabase with auth.
- Add full-text / vector search over transcripts for the `/search` experience.
- Replace manual extension token entry with a proper OAuth/session bridge and
  automatic token refresh; make the backend URL configurable.
- Add streaming upload + progress UI and large-file/long-meeting handling.
- Introduce automated tests (unit for libs/route handlers, e2e for auth + upload).
- Complete or remove the Electron desktop app and the TSX extension popup build
  path so `scripts/build.js` matches the repository contents.
- Add roles/sharing (team workspaces) on top of the per-user ownership model.
```
